description:
&lt;p&gt;The opportunity has arisen for an experienced nurse to join the Oncology Day Units within Northumbria Healthcare Foundation Trust. Northumbria has 5 units within the Trust offering quality, evidenced-based care to a wide variety of cancer patients undergoing chemotherapy and supportive care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicants should have a minimum of 5 years post registration experience, two of which should at a band 5/6 working with cancer patients. Previous experience with chemotherapy (N59 or equivalent) and an understanding of the complex needs of this patient group are essential. Advanced Clinical Assessment skills would be an advantage, and must be willing to undertake further training. The ability to support and develop junior members of the team is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should be able to demonstrate their ability to work autonomously, have excellent communication skills and well-developed personal coping strategies. Telephone on-call within the service rota, for patients receiving treatment, is part of the senior role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They must be willing to travel and have the ability to work as part of a small team, have the ability to maintain a sense of humour, and offer flexibility to meet the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sophie Atkinson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oncology Day Unit Manager&lt;/p&gt;
